==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cobæa
<hw>Co*b⟦ae⟧"a</hw></mhw>
<pr>(k⟦osl⟧*b⟦emac⟧"⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[Named after
<person>D. <etsep>Cobo</etsep></person>, a Spanish botanist.]</ety>
<def>A genus of climbing plants, native of Mexico and South America.
<spn>Cobaea scandens</spn> (called <stype>cup-and-saucer vine</stype>,
<stype>monastery bells</stype>, or <stype>Mexican ivy</stype>) is a
conservatory climber with large bell-shaped flowers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cobalt</ent>⟦br⟧
